The Makhado Police have asked the public to help them in their search for the 19-year-old Thabang Koloko. Koloko, who is a student at the Makhado Comprehensive School and stays at the Airforce Base Makhado, was last seen on Friday, 1 June. His uncle saw when Koloko departed for school. Koloko was wearing a blue v-neck jersey, a short sleeved white shirt, a pair of long grey trousers, black school shoes with grey shocks. Anyone that has information that can help to locate Koloko are urged to contact Const Tshifhiwa Netshiya at Tel 076 202 8972 or the Makhado Police Station at Tel 015 519 4300.